    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "2 Nephi",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "Joseph in Egypt saw the Nephites in vision\u2014He prophesied of Joseph Smith, the latter-day seer; of Moses, who would deliver Israel; and of the coming forth of the Book of Mormon. About 588\u2013570\u00a0B.C.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And now I speak unto you, Joseph, my last-born. Thou wast born in the wilderness of mine afflictions; yea, in the days of my greatest sorrow did thy mother bear thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 18:7 (7, 19).",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And may the Lord consecrate also unto thee this land, which is a most precious land, for thine inheritance and the inheritance of thy seed with thy brethren, for thy security forever, if it so be that ye shall keep the commandments of the Holy One of Israel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 2:20. TG\u00a0Promised Lands.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now, Joseph, my last-born, whom I have brought out of the wilderness of mine afflictions, may the Lord bless thee forever, for thy seed shall not utterly be destroyed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 45:7; 1\u00a0Ne. 13:30.",
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 139
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 9:8; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:53; 25:21.",
                        "start": 161,
                        "end": 170
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p3",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For behold, thou art the fruit of my loins; and I am a descendant of Joseph who was carried captive into Egypt. And great were the covenants of the Lord which he made unto Joseph.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 39:2; 45:4; 49:22 (22\u201326); Ps. 77:15; 1\u00a0Ne. 5:14 (14\u201316).",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 37:36 (29\u201336).",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 99
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 5:15.",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 140
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, Joseph truly saw our day. And he obtained a promise of the Lord, that out of the fruit of his loins the Lord God would raise up a righteous branch unto the house of Israel; not the Messiah, but a branch which was to be broken off, nevertheless, to be remembered in the covenants of the Lord that the Messiah should be made manifest unto them in the latter days, in the spirit of power, unto the bringing of them out of darkness unto light\u2014yea, out of hidden darkness and out of captivity unto freedom.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Gen. 50:24\u201338 (Bible Appendix); 2\u00a0Ne. 3:22; 4:2 (1\u201332).",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Promise.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 62
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jacob 2:25.",
                        "start": 141,
                        "end": 150
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 45:7 (5\u20137); 49:22 (22\u201326); 1\u00a0Ne. 15:12 (12, 16); 19:24; 2\u00a0Ne. 14:2. TG\u00a0Vineyard of the Lord.",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 157
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 6:14; D&C 3:18 (16\u201320).",
                        "start": 334,
                        "end": 342
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 42:16; 1\u00a0Jn. 2:8; 1\u00a0Ne. 21:9.",
                        "start": 430,
                        "end": 438
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For Joseph truly testified, saying: A seer shall the Lord my God raise up, who shall be a choice seer unto the fruit of my loins.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 21:11 (8\u201311); Morm. 8:16 (16, 25); Ether 3:28 (21\u201328). TG\u00a0Seer.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 132:30.",
                        "start": 123,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p6",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, Joseph truly said: Thus saith the Lord unto me: A choice seer will I raise up out of the fruit of thy loins; and he shall be esteemed highly among the fruit of thy loins. And unto him will I give commandment that he shall do a work for the fruit of thy loins, his brethren, which shall be of great worth unto them, even to the bringing of them to the knowledge of the covenants which I have made with thy fathers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Joseph Smith.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Millennium, Preparing a People for.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Book of Mormon.",
                        "start": 356,
                        "end": 365
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will give unto him a commandment that he shall do none other work, save the work which I shall command him. And I will make him great in mine eyes; for he shall do my work.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 24:9 (8\u20139).",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he shall be great like unto Moses, whom I have said I would raise up unto you, to deliver my people, O house of Israel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:41.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 3:10 (7\u201310); 1\u00a0Ne. 17:24.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 93
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 29:14.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Moses will I raise up, to deliver thy people out of the land of Egypt.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Foreordination.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But a seer will I raise up out of the fruit of thy loins; and unto him will I give power to bring forth my word unto the seed of thy loins\u2014and not to the bringing forth my word only, saith the Lord, but to the convincing them of my word, which shall have already gone forth among them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 21:8; 3\u00a0Ne. 21:11 (8\u201311); Morm. 8:16 (16, 25). TG\u00a0Prophets, Mission of.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 5:4 (3\u20134).",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures to Come Forth.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 61
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, the fruit of thy loins shall write; and the fruit of the loins of Judah shall write; and that which shall be written by the fruit of thy loins, and also that which shall be written by the fruit of the loins of Judah, shall grow together, unto the confounding of false doctrines and laying down of contentions, and establishing peace among the fruit of thy loins, and bringing them to the knowledge of their fathers in the latter days, and also to the knowledge of my covenants, saith the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Book of Mormon.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 13:23 (23\u201329); 2\u00a0Ne. 29:12.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Preservation of; Scriptures, Writing of.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 94
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 37:17 (15\u201320); 1\u00a0Ne. 13:39 (38\u201341); 2\u00a0Ne. 29:8; 33:10 (10\u201311).",
                        "start": 258,
                        "end": 269
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0False Doctrine.",
                        "start": 273,
                        "end": 288
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peacemakers.",
                        "start": 338,
                        "end": 343
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moro. 1:4.",
                        "start": 378,
                        "end": 386
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 15:14; 2\u00a0Ne. 30:5; 3\u00a0Ne. 5:23; Morm. 7:9 (1, 5, 9\u201310).",
                        "start": 399,
                        "end": 408
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p12",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And out of weakness he shall be made strong, in that day when my work shall commence among all my people, unto the restoring thee, O house of Israel, saith the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And thus prophesied Joseph, saying: Behold, that seer will the Lord bless; and they that seek to destroy him shall be confounded; for this promise, which I have obtained of the Lord, of the fruit of my loins, shall be fulfilled. Behold, I am sure of the fulfilling of this promise;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And his name shall be called after me; and it shall be after the name of his father. And he shall be like unto me; for the thing, which the Lord shall bring forth by his hand, by the power of the Lord shall bring my people unto salvation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 18:8.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JS\u2014H 1:3.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 28:2.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 105
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Enos 1:13 (12\u201318); Alma 37:19 (1\u201320).",
                        "start": 213,
                        "end": 215
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Value of.",
                        "start": 228,
                        "end": 237
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, thus prophesied Joseph: I am sure of this thing, even as I am sure of the promise of Moses; for the Lord hath said unto me, I will preserve thy seed forever.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 45:7 (1\u20138); D&C 107:42.",
                        "start": 136,
                        "end": 144
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord hath said: I will raise up a Moses; and I will give power unto him in a rod; and I will give judgment unto him in writing. Yet I will not loose his tongue, that he shall speak much, for I will not make him mighty in speaking. But I will write unto him my law, by the finger of mine own hand; and I will make a spokesman for him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 10:2 (2, 4); Moses 2:1. TG\u00a0Scriptures, Writing of.",
                        "start": 250,
                        "end": 255
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 4:16 (14\u201316).",
                        "start": 323,
                        "end": 332
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord said unto me also: I will raise up unto the fruit of thy loins; and I will make for him a spokesman. And I, behold, I will give unto him that he shall write the writing of the fruit of thy loins, unto the fruit of thy loins; and the spokesman of thy loins shall declare it.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the words which he shall write shall be the words which are expedient in my wisdom should go forth unto the fruit of thy loins. And it shall be as if the fruit of thy loins had cried unto them from the dust; for I know their faith.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 28:8.",
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 117
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 29:4; 2\u00a0Ne. 27:13; 33:13 (13\u201315); Morm. 9:30; Moro. 10:27.",
                        "start": 197,
                        "end": 201
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they shall cry from the dust; yea, even repentance unto their brethren, even after many generations have gone by them. And it shall come to pass that their cry shall go, even according to the simpleness of their words.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 26:16; Morm. 8:23 (23, 26).",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Book of Mormon.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Because of their faith their words shall proceed forth out of my mouth unto their brethren who are the fruit of thy loins; and the weakness of their words will I make strong in their faith, unto the remembering of my covenant which I made unto thy fathers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 29:2.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 62
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now, behold, my son Joseph, after this manner did my father of old prophesy.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 3:5.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, because of this covenant thou art blessed; for thy seed shall not be destroyed, for they shall hearken unto the words of the book.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Birthright.",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Obedience.",
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And there shall rise up one mighty among them, who shall do much good, both in word and in deed, being an instrument in the hands of God, with exceeding faith, to work mighty wonders, and do that thing which is great in the sight of God, unto the bringing to pass much restoration unto the house of Israel, and unto the seed of thy brethren.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Joseph Smith.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Dispensations; Israel, Restoration of; Restoration of the Gospel.",
                        "start": 269,
                        "end": 280
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now, blessed art thou, Joseph. Behold, thou art little; wherefore hearken unto the words of thy brother, Nephi, and it shall be done unto thee even according to the words which I have spoken. Remember the words of thy dying father. Amen.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}